abstract: New York Jets rookie linebacker Lorenzo Mauldin, who sustained spinal injury after what appeared to be head-to-head collision in team's season-opening victory over Cleveland Browns, is set to play in upcoming game against Philadelphia Eagles.
lead_paragraph: The Jets had feared Lorenzo Mauldin sustained a spinal injury after what appeared to be a head-to-head collision.

headline.main: Two Weeks After Scare, Jets Rookie Is Set to Return
headline.print_headline: Two Weeks After Scare, Jets Rookie Is Set to Return
